description: From Middle English ensaumple (noun) and ensaumplen (verb), from Old French ensample.

entries.meaning: (archaic) An example; a pattern or model for imitation.

verbs.description: ensample (third-person singular simple present ensamples, present participle ensampling, simple past and past participle ensampled)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To exemplify, to show by example.
